Sentencas: Mixed ionic and electronic conductors (MIEC) such as LSM (La0.7Sr0.3MnO3-delta), LSCM (La0.7Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-delta) and BSCF (Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta) have been investigated as potential cathode materials with La6WO12 (LWO) proton conducting electrolyte for use in protonic ceramic fuel cells (PCFC).
Titulo: Compatibility of proton conducting La6WO12 electrolyte with standard cathode materials

Sentencas: Different cathode - LWO powder mixtures have been subjected to high temperature treatment (1150 degrees C during 144 h in air) and studied by X-ray powder diffraction (XRPD) and scanning electron microscopy (SEM).
Titulo: Compatibility of proton conducting La6WO12 electrolyte with standard cathode materials

Sentencas: The analysis of the results reveals that LWO is chemically and mechanically stable with LSM and LSCM but reacts with BSCF.
Titulo: Compatibility of proton conducting La6WO12 electrolyte with standard cathode materials

Sentencas: Symmetrical cells cathode/LWO/cathode have been studied by electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS).
Titulo: Compatibility of proton conducting La6WO12 electrolyte with standard cathode materials
